; Nonlinear transitive closure with a base rule, exercised so that BOTH
; same-stratum body-atom positions of the recursive rule change in the
; SAME batch (both-added, both-deleted, and one-added/one-deleted
; crossings across separate batches). The FLAG-F/FLAG-H discriminator:
; p(X,Z) : p(X,Y), p(Y,Z) has TWO same-stratum positions (p at position 0
; and p at position 1 of the join), so a same-round double-claim of BOTH
; positions is reachable, which is exactly the shape FLAG-H's "one
; emission per delta position" vs "single emission, dynamic dispatch"
; question needs, and exactly the shape that requires
; SurvivesSoFar/AliveAtClaim (or InNewWithFrontier/InNewSansFrontier) to
; differ from InNew/InI for a wrong resolution to be visible in the final
; state.
#message add_edge(u64 From, u64 To) @differential.
#query reachable(free u64 From, free u64 To).
#local p(From, To).
#local edge(From, To).

edge(From, To) : add_edge(From, To).

p(From, To) : edge(From, To).
p(From, To) : p(From, Y), p(Y, To).

reachable(From, To) : p(From, To).
